Business Brief -- Cincinnati Milacron Inc.:
   First-Quarter Net Posted;
   Profitable 1992 Is Expected
For 1991, Milacron had a net loss of $100.2 million, or
$3.67 a share, on sales of $754 million, compared with a net
loss of $24.3 million, or 95 cents a share, on sales of $805
million in 1990. The 1991 net loss includes nonrecurring
charges of $90 million to relocate certain machine-tool
product lines and to write down the value of the company's
measurement equipment unit for its eventual sale.